---
---

<section id="architecture" class="relative border-y border-border-subtle bg-surface-dark py-24 md:py-32">
  <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0">
    <div class="grid-pattern absolute inset-0 opacity-50"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6">
    <div class="mb-16 text-center">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        The <span class="gradient-text">BFF Pattern</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-lg text-text-muted">
        Your frontend never talks to the backend directly. Every request flows through a secure BFF proxy layer with token forwarding and CSRF protection.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Architecture diagram -->
    <div class="glow mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <div class="code-block">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 border-b border-border-subtle px-4 py-3">
          <span class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-red-500/60"></span>
          <span class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-yellow-500/60"></span>
          <span class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-green-500/60"></span>
          <span class="ml-3 text-xs text-text-muted">architecture.txt</span>
        </div>
        <pre class="!text-sm !leading-loose"><code>
<span class="text-violet-300">Browser</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  |</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  |  HTTPS (cookies, CSRF token)</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  |</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  |--- </span><span class="text-indigo-400">Next.js BFF</span>          <span class="text-text-muted">:3001  (App Router, RSC)</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  |</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  '--- </span><span class="text-pink-400">TanStack Start BFF</span>   <span class="text-text-muted">:3003  (Vite, TanStack Router)</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">          |</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">          |  Bearer token  +  Cookie forwarding</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">          |</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">          |--- </span><span class="text-amber-400">Laravel API</span>     <span class="text-text-muted">:8000  (BetterAuth, Bearer tokens)</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">          |</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">          |--- </span><span class="text-sky-400">Symfony API</span>     <span class="text-text-muted">:8002  (BetterAuth, Paseto V4)</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">          |</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">          '--- </span><span class="text-emerald-400">Hono API</span>        <span class="text-text-muted">:8003  (JWT, HS256)</span>
</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Benefits row -->
    <div class="mt-14 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="mb-2 text-2xl font-bold text-violet-400">1</div>
        <h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold">Single Entry Point</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">All API calls go through the BFF. No CORS issues, no exposed backend URLs.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="mb-2 text-2xl font-bold text-violet-400">2</div>
        <h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold">Token Secured</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Every request from the BFF to the backend carries the user's Bearer token with CSRF validation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="mb-2 text-2xl font-bold text-violet-400">3</div>
        <h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold">Swap Backends</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Change one env var to switch between Laravel, Symfony, or Hono. Zero frontend changes.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature Slices -->
    <div class="mt-20">
      <h3 class="mb-6 text-center text-xl font-semibold">
        <span class="gradient-text">Vertical Slice</span> Architecture
      </h3>
      <p class="mx-auto mb-8 max-w-2xl text-center text-sm text-text-muted">
        Each domain module is a self-contained vertical slice with its own routes, controllers, services, and models.
      </p>
      <div class="glow mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <div class="code-block">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 border-b border-border-subtle px-4 py-3">
            <span class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-red-500/60"></span>
            <span class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-yellow-500/60"></span>
            <span class="h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-green-500/60"></span>
            <span class="ml-3 text-xs text-text-muted">feature-slices.txt</span>
          </div>
          <pre class="!text-sm !leading-loose"><code>
<span class="text-violet-300">Features/</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  |</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  |--- </span><span class="text-violet-400">Auth</span>          <span class="text-text-muted">Login, Register, 2FA, OAuth, Password Reset</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  |--- </span><span class="text-amber-400">Shop</span>          <span class="text-text-muted">Products, Categories, Reviews</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  |--- </span><span class="text-amber-400">Cart</span>          <span class="text-text-muted">Add, Update, Remove Items</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  |--- </span><span class="text-amber-400">Orders</span>        <span class="text-text-muted">Checkout, History, Status</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  |--- </span><span class="text-sky-400">Admin</span>         <span class="text-text-muted">RBAC, Dashboard, Analytics, Inventory</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  |--- </span><span class="text-emerald-400">SaaS</span>          <span class="text-text-muted">Orgs, Plans, Billing, Teams</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  '--- </span><span class="text-pink-400">Support</span>       <span class="text-text-muted">Conversations, Messages, Agent Queue</span>

<span class="text-violet-300">Shared/</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  |--- Models / Entities    (User, Role, Permission)</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  |--- Middleware / Security (Auth guard, CORS)</span>
<span class="text-text-muted">  '--- Services             (Mailer, Storage)</span>
</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
